Using REXX generate a de Brujin pattern. This REXX script is courtesy of Davide Girardi and available here: https://gist.github.com/davidegirardi/61385ae404f4306349167ac1483b40b9#file-brujin-rex

# Exit ISPF (hit `F3` until you're at the READY prompt or you can exit ISPF by putting `=x` on the command line) and run `RX DEBRUJIN 20`. This rexx script is stored in `<username>.EXEC(DEBRUJIN)`.  [img[debrujinrexx.png]]
# Open up ISPF again and edit `<username>.JCLLIB(LAB06)`. 
# Notice that all this JCL is doing is running the DEBRUJIN script and generating 1000 characters.
# Submit this job to place those 1000 characters in `DC00.OVERFLOW.ARBAUTH(DEBRUJIN)`
# The job should return with `MAX COND CODE 0000`

